**Version Used**: Visual Studio 17.12.3

**Steps to Reproduce**:

1. In Visual Studio, create a new class library project.
2. Add a new ".editorconfig" file.  Ensure that it contains the following:
    ```
    dotnet_style_parentheses_in_other_binary_operators = always_for_clarity
    ```
3. Add a method to `Class1`:
    ```C#
    namespace ClassLibrary1;

    public class Class1
    {
        public static bool M()
        {
            return (1 | (1 & 1)) == 1;
        }
    }
    ```
4. Create a new folder in the project named "N".
5. Move "Class1.cs" to "N".  When prompted for "Adjust namespace for moved file?", click "Yes".

Alternatively:

5. Move "Class1.cs" to "N".  When prompted for "Adjust namespace for moved file?", click "No".
6. Open "Quick Actions" on line 1 and select "Change namespace to match folder structure".

**Expected Behavior**:

The parentheses are preserved.  (This was the behavior prior to .NET 9.)

**Actual Behavior**:

The parentheses around the `&` subexpression are removed.
```C#
namespace ClassLibrary1.N;

public class Class1
{
    public static bool M()
    {
        return (1 | 1 & 1) == 1;
    }
}
```
